    "created_at": "2013-07-09T21:46:18Z",
    "updated_at": "2013-07-09T21:46:18Z",
    "body": "@bblum is correct, on x86 it will be hard or impossible to see the difference between the stronger and weaker atomics (and in some cases, even between atomics and non-atomics) because the architecture already has very strong guarantees. This presentation might be relevant:\nhttp://channel9.msdn.com/Shows/Going+Deep/Cpp-and-Beyond-2012-Herb-Sutter-atomic-Weapons-1-of-2\nhttp://channel9.msdn.com/Shows/Going+Deep/Cpp-and-Beyond-2012-Herb-Sutter-atomic-Weapons-2-of-2\nAbout a third in the second video some architectures are compared.\n",
